President Biden held a meeting with members of his Invest in America Cabinet to discuss the progress of major legislation and the growth of the economy. He highlighted positive job numbers, with 250,000 jobs added last month and the unemployment rate at a 50-year low. He emphasized the importance of investing in America and bringing back the supply chain to the United States. The President expressed concern about the threat of defaulting on the debt and criticized Republicans for tying the debt limit to their budget plan, which he said would have detrimental effects on various sectors, including healthcare and law enforcement. He urged Congress to pass the debt limit and engage in open debates about spending and taxation. President Biden mentioned the upcoming press conference and declined to comment on Russia's allegation that the US was behind a drone attack.